WEBVTT

00:00.201 --> 00:01.102
PREVIOUSLY ON REAPER...

00:01.102 --> 00:02.273
ERIC SOLD MY SOUL
TO THE DEVIL

00:02.273 --> 00:03.104
AND I ASKED
FOR HELP.

00:03.104 --> 00:05.005
YOU DIDN'T TELL ANDI?
NO! I'M NOT
GONNA TELL ANDI.

00:05.005 --> 00:06.177
IF SHE KNOWS, SHE'LL
THINK I'M A FREAK.

00:06.177 --> 00:07.438
SHE'LL NEVER
GO OUT WITH ME.

00:07.438 --> 00:08.609
FLOWERS AREN'T FROM ME.

00:08.609 --> 00:09.340
NO, THEY'RE FROM GREG.

00:09.340 --> 00:12.583
I KNOW YOU'VE BEEN DISTRACTED
BY ALL THIS GREG BUSINESS,

00:12.583 --> 00:15.586
SO I TOOK THE LIBERTY
TO DIG UP SOME DIRT ON HIM.

00:15.586 --> 00:19.120
WELL, YOU KNOW, GREG'S DATING
TWINS, OK? 2 SLUTTY TWINS.

00:19.120 --> 00:20.020
THEY'RE HIS SISTERS.

00:20.020 --> 00:22.323
SOMEONE GAVE ME
THE WRONG INFORMATION.
WHO?

00:22.323 --> 00:24.255
WHO WOULD SAY THAT?

00:25.025 --> 00:27.328
[WATER RUNNING]

00:32.032 --> 00:34.165
[DOOR OPENS]

00:37.108 --> 00:39.270
HE'S IN THE BATHROOM.

00:39.270 --> 00:43.614
OH, MAN.
LOOK AT THAT CRAZY.

00:45.376 --> 00:49.049
HEY, THESE ARE ALL ABOUT
THE WORLD TRADE ORGANIZATION...

00:49.049 --> 00:50.551
THE G-8 SUMMIT.

00:50.551 --> 00:52.623
HEY, WAIT.
WHAT WAS THIS SOUL GONNA DO?

00:52.623 --> 00:57.558
SAM! SAM, CAN I HAVE THIS
AFTER WE CAPTURE HIM?

00:57.558 --> 01:00.131
♪ ALOHA ♪

01:00.131 --> 01:00.561
SOCK!

01:00.561 --> 01:02.193
Leon: HEY, WHO'S OUT THERE?

01:02.193 --> 01:05.566
THIS IS A PRIVATE
RESIDENCE! I DON'T THINK
YOU CAN BE IN HERE.

01:05.566 --> 01:06.767
LEON, GET OUT HERE!

01:06.767 --> 01:08.639
Leon: LISTEN,
I'M ALL BETTER NOW.

01:08.639 --> 01:10.171
I'M NOT KILLING
ANYBODY ANYMORE.

01:10.171 --> 01:12.343
WE CAN SEE YOUR WALL
OF INSANITY, OK?

01:12.343 --> 01:13.504
WE KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE PLANNING.

01:13.504 --> 01:16.347
Leon: NO, NO!
THAT'S MY THOUGHT BOARD.

01:16.347 --> 01:17.308
MY THERAPIST TOLD ME
TO MAKE IT.

01:17.308 --> 01:20.281
DO WE HAVE TO COME IN THERE
OR ARE YOU GONNA COME OUT?

01:20.281 --> 01:24.455
Leon: WELL...
OK, THEN.

01:31.562 --> 01:34.825
I WANT YOU GUYS TO KNOW
I'VE WORKED VERY HARD

01:34.825 --> 01:36.297
ON MY
PSYCHOLOGICAL HEALTH,

01:36.297 --> 01:39.270
SO WHAT I'M ABOUT TO DO
IS VERY DIFFICULT FOR ME.

01:39.270 --> 01:40.831
IT'S REALLY GOING
TO HURT MY HEART.

01:40.831 --> 01:45.176
THERE'S NO FREAKING WAY
I'M GOING BACK TO HELL.

01:45.176 --> 01:46.607
AAH!

01:47.878 --> 01:49.810
[SCREAMING]

02:04.595 --> 02:09.300
WELL, THIS JUST KEEPS
GETTING EASIER AND EASIER.

02:22.173 --> 02:23.914
WOW. I'M NOT USUALLY
A MORNING PERSON,

02:23.914 --> 02:25.516
BUT I KIND OF LIKE KNOCKING
A SOUL OFF FIRST THING.

02:25.516 --> 02:27.448
GET THE REST
OF THE DAY TO MYSELF.

02:27.448 --> 02:28.549
I KNEW THAT GUY
WAS GOING DOWN EASY.

02:28.549 --> 02:32.152
HE CAME OUT, WE SUCKED HIS
ASS UP, AND BOOM, END OF STORY.

02:32.152 --> 02:33.184
SOCK, WE ALMOST
GOT KILLED.

02:33.184 --> 02:36.857
WHATEVER. WE'VE ALMOST BEEN
KILLED WAY WORSE THAN THAT.

02:37.828 --> 02:42.433
UH, SAM, WHERE'S GLADYS?

02:42.433 --> 02:44.795
CAN I HELP YOU?

02:46.597 --> 02:49.540
YEAH.
IS GLADYS HERE?

02:49.540 --> 02:51.202
ON VACATION.

02:51.202 --> 02:51.942
OH.

02:51.942 --> 02:54.245
DO YOU KNOW WHEN
SHE'LL BE BACK?

02:54.245 --> 02:55.346
NO.

02:55.346 --> 02:58.209
IS THERE SOMETHING
I CAN HELP YOU WITH?

02:58.209 --> 03:00.411
UM...

03:02.853 --> 03:03.914
THAT?

03:03.914 --> 03:07.288
I'M JUST WONDERING IF
YOU WANT TO TAKE THAT.

03:07.288 --> 03:08.759
DO I WANT YOUR SNOW GLOBE?

03:08.759 --> 03:12.893
I MEAN, IS THERE
A PLACE WHERE STUFF LIKE
THIS GETS TURNED IN?

03:12.893 --> 03:17.598
SIR, THIS IS THE DEPARTMENT
OF MOTOR VEHICLES.

03:17.598 --> 03:19.770
RIGHT, RIGHT.

03:19.770 --> 03:23.203
IS THERE ANYBODY ELSE
WHO COULD MAYBE HELP US?

03:24.835 --> 03:26.477
ROGER.

03:29.740 --> 03:32.583
DO YOU WANT
HIS SNOW GLOBE?

03:33.714 --> 03:35.816
YEAH, I'LL TAKE THAT.

03:35.816 --> 03:37.217
AHEM. MM-MMM.

03:37.217 --> 03:39.920
I'M JUST GONNA COME
BACK ANOTHER TIME.

03:39.920 --> 03:40.991
THANKS, GUYS.

03:40.991 --> 03:42.993
THANK YOU.

03:44.395 --> 03:48.699
HALLOWEEN IS AN EXTREMELY
IMPORTANT HOLIDAY TO ME.

03:48.699 --> 03:54.234
THE ONE TIME OF YEAR WHEN
A PERSON ALLOWS HIS FEELINGS
TO TAKE FLIGHT...

03:54.234 --> 03:57.968
HIS WISHES AND DESIRES
TO BE KNOWN TO THE WORLD.

03:57.968 --> 04:03.013
TED, UH, YOU DO REALIZE
HALLOWEEN IS STILL
TWO DAYS AWAY?

04:03.013 --> 04:05.646
HALLOWEEN IS NOT A DAY, OK?
IT'S A SEASON.

04:05.646 --> 04:09.320
WHICH BRINGS ME
TO MY SPECIAL TREAT.

04:09.720 --> 04:12.853
WHO WANTS TO BE
OUR LUCKY PUMPKIN? HUH?

04:12.853 --> 04:13.484
OH, COME ON, GUYS.

04:13.484 --> 04:16.557
YOU GET TO DRESS UP AS
A BEAUTIFUL PUMPKIN AND
BRING JOY TO CHILDREN...

04:16.557 --> 04:18.429
AND PASS OUT COUPONS.

04:18.429 --> 04:20.731
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO BE
THE PUMPKIN, SOCK.

04:20.731 --> 04:22.633
RACIST.

04:22.633 --> 04:25.466
ANDI. HEY.

04:25.466 --> 04:26.597
OUCH.

04:26.597 --> 04:27.638
SHE STILL MAD AT YOU?

04:27.638 --> 04:29.970
ANDI! ANDI, COME ON.

04:29.970 --> 04:31.842
ANDI, YES!
YOU CAN BE THE PUMPKIN.

04:31.842 --> 04:36.577
NO. I REALLY DON'T WANT
TO BE THE PUMPKIN, TED.

04:36.577 --> 04:39.310
I-I'LL BE THE PUMPKIN. I'LL...

04:39.310 --> 04:40.411
ME. NOT HER.

04:40.411 --> 04:40.951
OK. SORRY, ANDI.

04:40.951 --> 04:44.284
I GUESS SAM WANTS
IT MORE THAN YOU.

04:46.587 --> 04:50.661
OK. I GOT SOMETHING
SERIOUSLY COOL
TO SHOW YOU GUYS.

04:52.893 --> 04:55.496
ALL RIGHT. YOU READY?

04:57.968 --> 05:01.702
SOCK, STOP MESSING
WITH THE VESSEL.

05:01.702 --> 05:03.974
SHH, SHH! OK. DO IT!

05:03.974 --> 05:08.409
Leon: UH...WHAT DO
YOU WANT ME TO SAY?

05:09.880 --> 05:12.413
IT TALKS!

05:12.413 --> 05:13.484
WOW.
I KNOW!

05:13.484 --> 05:15.546
I KNOW. I HEARD IT
COMING FROM SAM'S LOCKER.

05:15.546 --> 05:17.618
HOW'D YOU GET
INTO MY LOCKER?

05:17.618 --> 05:18.318
OH, BOLT CUTTERS.

05:18.318 --> 05:20.351
LOOK, I THINK I'M GONNA HIDE
IT IN TED'S PRIVATE BATHROOM

05:20.351 --> 05:23.023
SO HE THINKS
THE TOILET'S TALKING TO HIM.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

05:23.023 --> 05:24.655
NO. WE'RE NOT
DOING THAT.

05:24.655 --> 05:25.926
Leon: I'LL DO THAT.

05:25.926 --> 05:26.857
JUST LEAVE
IT ALONE. OK?

05:26.857 --> 05:28.459
WE DON'T WANT
TO BREAK IT.

05:28.459 --> 05:29.700
Leon: LISTEN, I WAS
JUST WONDERING,

05:29.700 --> 05:31.962
ANY CHANCE I CAN
GET OUT OF HERE

05:31.962 --> 05:32.903
FOR THERAPY
AT 3:00 TODAY?

05:32.903 --> 05:34.705
NO, I AM NOT
LETTING YOU OUT.

05:34.705 --> 05:35.606
Leon: WELL, WHY NOT?

05:35.606 --> 05:37.738
UH, LET'S START WITH
THE ORIGINAL PROBLEM.

05:37.738 --> 05:38.939
LEON, YOU WERE
AN ASSASSIN.

05:38.939 --> 05:41.942
Leon: YOU MEAN SHOOTING
PRESIDENT McKINLEY?

05:41.942 --> 05:43.744
ARE YOU GOING TO HOLD
THAT AGAINST ME?

05:43.744 --> 05:44.815
YES, YES, I AM.

05:44.815 --> 05:46.647
Leon: THAT WAS
A HUNDRED YEARS AGO.

05:46.647 --> 05:47.978
I'M COMPLETELY
OVER THAT NOW.

05:47.978 --> 05:51.922
I'VE BEEN OUT OF HELL
OVER A YEAR. I HAVEN'T
TRIED TO HURT ANYBODY.

05:51.922 --> 05:53.053
YOU SHOT AT US.

05:53.053 --> 05:54.785
Leon: SELF-DEFENSE!

05:55.886 --> 05:57.958
LEON, YOU'RE GOING
BACK TO HELL.

05:57.958 --> 05:58.889
DO NO TOUCH HIM.

05:58.889 --> 06:01.392
OH, COME ON, SAM.
Leon: WHY ARE YOU DOING
THIS? WHY DO YOU CARE?

06:01.392 --> 06:03.694
BECAUSE HE'S THE DEVIL'S
BOUNTY HUNTER.

06:03.694 --> 06:04.995
Leon: YOU GOT
THAT RIGHT, SOCK.

06:04.995 --> 06:09.039
THIS GUY REALLY DOES
HAVE A STICK UP HIS ASS.

06:09.039 --> 06:09.770
STICK UP MY ASS?

06:09.770 --> 06:11.101
WHAT ARE YOU, TALKING
ABOUT ME BEHIND MY BACK?

06:11.101 --> 06:13.003
NO, NO, IT WAS A JOKE.

06:13.003 --> 06:16.977
BUT DOESN'T EVERY JOKE HAVE
A GRAIN OF TRUTH TO IT?

06:16.977 --> 06:18.949
DON'T TOUCH IT.

06:29.420 --> 06:31.492
HEY, WHAT'S UP?

06:32.593 --> 06:33.924
STOCKING THE CANDY, HUH?

06:33.924 --> 06:35.866
YEP.

06:37.498 --> 06:40.000
ALL RIGHT. IS THAT
WHAT WE'RE DOING NOW?

06:40.000 --> 06:42.673
ONE-WORD ANSWERS?

06:43.504 --> 06:45.035
ANDI, COME ON.

06:45.035 --> 06:47.808
I DIDN'T MEAN TO SABOTAGE
YOU AND GREG.

06:47.808 --> 06:49.009
I'M SORRY I EVEN
GOT INVOLVED.

06:49.009 --> 06:53.013
I WAS JUST--
I WAS TRULY JUST TRYING
TO BE YOUR FRIEND.

06:53.013 --> 06:57.988
WHAT CAN I DO
TO MAKE THIS UP TO YOU?
I'LL DO ANYTHING. NAME IT.

06:57.988 --> 06:59.950
I JUST CAN'T.

07:00.991 --> 07:02.693
CAN'T WHAT?

07:02.693 --> 07:04.725
IT'S NOT WHAT YOU SAID
ABOUT GREG, OK?

07:04.725 --> 07:06.597
IT'S WHAT
THAT SAID ABOUT US.

07:06.597 --> 07:08.428
AND IF YOU COULD DO
SOMETHING LIKE THAT,

07:08.428 --> 07:13.964
THEN MAYBE OUR
FRIENDSHIP ISN'T WHAT
I THOUGHT IT WAS.

07:13.964 --> 07:19.540
HONESTLY, I JUST REALLY
DON'T KNOW HOW TO BE
FRIENDS WITH YOU ANYMORE.

07:21.141 --> 07:24.915
OH. THAT'S A PROBLEM.

07:26.477 --> 07:29.079
I JUST--I CAN'T.

07:44.935 --> 07:47.538
[DOG GROWLING]

07:51.502 --> 07:53.544
WHAT THE...

08:03.253 --> 08:04.985
[THUNDER]

08:09.920 --> 08:11.992
[DOG BARKS]

08:11.992 --> 08:13.924
HELLO, SPIKE.

08:13.924 --> 08:17.998
PERFECT TIMING, BECAUSE MY
DAY DIDN'T SUCK ENOUGH YET.

08:17.998 --> 08:19.930
SURPRISE.

08:19.930 --> 08:22.232
WHAT'S UP?

08:23.273 --> 08:25.706
VERY LITTLE.

08:27.908 --> 08:30.711
O-KAY.

08:31.211 --> 08:35.015
THIS IS GONNA SOUND
WEIRD, BUT ARE YOU
ALL RIGHT?

08:35.215 --> 08:38.218
HOLIDAYS ALWAYS
DEPRESS ME, SAM.

08:38.218 --> 08:40.020
HOLIDAYS?

08:40.020 --> 08:41.191
WHAT? HALLOWEEN?

08:41.191 --> 08:43.994
I THOUGHT YOU'D LOVE
THIS TIME OF YEAR.

08:43.994 --> 08:46.727
I DETEST IT WITH
EVERY FIBER OF MY BEING.

08:46.727 --> 08:50.961
BACK WHEN IT WAS THE ANCIENT
CELTIC FESTIVAL OF SAMHAIN...

08:50.961 --> 08:54.605
NOW THAT--THAT WAS A HOLIDAY.

08:54.605 --> 08:57.067
DEAD RISING
FROM THEIR GRAVES...

08:57.067 --> 09:00.971
DAMAGING CROPS,
CAUSING TROUBLE.

09:00.971 --> 09:03.043
GOOD TIMES.

09:03.313 --> 09:04.575
BUT NOW YOU HATE IT.

09:04.575 --> 09:06.076
IT'S THE COMMERCIALIZATION
OF EVIL.

09:06.076 --> 09:13.283
THE ONE DAY WHEN NOT
A SOUL ON EARTH FEARS ME,
OR EVEN BELIEVES IN ME.

09:13.283 --> 09:15.926
I BECOME A PARTY GAG.

09:15.926 --> 09:18.989
A PLASTIC MASK.

09:18.989 --> 09:20.731
IT'S ONLY ONE DAY
OUT OF THE YEAR.

09:20.731 --> 09:23.994
ARE YOU TRYING TO MAKE
ME FEEL BETTER, SAM?

09:24.835 --> 09:27.137
YEAH. I GUESS I AM.

09:27.137 --> 09:27.868
HOW WEIRD.

09:27.868 --> 09:33.704
IN ANY EVENT, I LET HELL TAKE
A HOLIDAY ON HALLOWEEN.

09:33.704 --> 09:36.146
THEN EVERYTHING
GRINDS TO A HALT,

09:36.146 --> 09:37.577
PAPERWORK GETS BACKS UP.

09:37.577 --> 09:40.981
A FEW DAYS OF VACATION SETS
ME BACK A HUNDRED YEARS.

09:40.981 --> 09:41.952
IT'S A NIGHTMARE.

09:41.952 --> 09:45.155
AHH. THAT'S WHY I
COULDN'T TURN IN LEON.

09:45.155 --> 09:47.988
THE DMV DEMON
WAS ON VACATION.

09:47.988 --> 09:48.789
[CHUCKLES]

09:48.789 --> 09:53.794
THE WHOLE THING
MAKES ME SICK.

09:53.994 --> 09:57.267
YOU WANT TO HEAR
A REALLY SCARY STORY?

10:02.602 --> 10:04.775
[DOOR CREAKING]

10:04.775 --> 10:07.277
THIS USED TO BE
A SLAUGHTERHOUSE.

10:07.277 --> 10:10.040
TURN OF THE CENTURY
THEY WERE BUTCHERING

10:10.040 --> 10:12.813
A THOUSAND HEAD
OF CATTLE A DAY.

10:12.813 --> 10:13.984
AND WHEN IT RAINED,

10:13.984 --> 10:16.616
THE STREETS WOULD
RUN RED WITH BLOOD.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.348
AHH. THEN IN THE 1940s,

10:18.348 --> 10:21.692
A SERIAL KILLER TERRORIZED
THIS NEIGHBORHOOD.

10:21.692 --> 10:23.253
UNDER THE COVER OF NIGHT.

10:23.253 --> 10:25.656
HE CHOSE EASY VICTIMS...

10:25.656 --> 10:27.357
YOU KNOW, RUNAWAYS...

10:27.357 --> 10:28.959
VAGRANTS...

10:28.959 --> 10:30.260
PROSTITUTES.

10:30.260 --> 10:32.032
HE BROUGHT THEM ALL HERE.

10:32.032 --> 10:34.634
THEY CALLED HIM THE BUTCHER.

10:34.634 --> 10:36.707
[DOG BARKING]

10:36.707 --> 10:38.108
AND THIS LITTLE GUY,

10:38.108 --> 10:38.939
HE WAS ON THE TORTURE TEAM

10:38.939 --> 10:40.070
FOR THE BUTCHER
DOWN IN HELL.

10:40.070 --> 10:44.945
SPIKE MAY NOT
LOOK LIKE MUCH, BUT CAN
HE MAKE GROWN MEN CRY.

10:44.945 --> 10:46.146
SO THE BUTCHER'S
ON THE LOOSE?

10:46.146 --> 10:48.418
HE'S ALREADY
CLAIMED ONE VICTIM.

10:48.418 --> 10:52.082
AND HE'S GOING TO
TRY TO KILL AGAIN.

10:52.082 --> 10:52.883
HERE.

10:52.883 --> 10:54.985
POLICE FINALLY CAUGHT
THE BUTCHER,

10:54.985 --> 10:58.689
BUT THEY NEVER FOUND
ANY OF HIS VICTIMS.

10:58.689 --> 11:03.894
THERE WERE RUMORS ABOUT
WHAT HE DID WITH THE BODIES.

11:10.170 --> 11:12.372
[DOG GROWLING]

11:14.705 --> 11:15.976
UH!

11:15.976 --> 11:17.948
[DOG BARKING]

11:34.324 --> 11:35.365
OH, NO!

11:35.365 --> 11:37.097
[LAUGHTER]

11:47.207 --> 11:50.380
SHE IS CRYING HER EYES
OUT ON THE INSIDE, MAN.

11:51.211 --> 11:53.343
YEAH, SOMEHOW I DOUBT THAT.

11:53.343 --> 11:56.286
OH, COME ON, YOU GUYS
CAN HANDLE THIS.

11:56.286 --> 11:57.347
YOU MADE A TINY
LITTLE MISTAKE.

11:57.347 --> 11:58.819
SHE'S GOTTA FORGIVE YOU
SOONER OR LATER.

11:58.819 --> 12:01.852
SHE DOESN'T TRUST ME.
SHE THINKS I'M A LIAR.

12:01.852 --> 12:02.853
I CAN'T BLAME HER.

12:02.853 --> 12:04.354
YEAH. OH, HERE,
BY THE WAY.

12:04.354 --> 12:07.227
TOOK HIM WITH ME TO
TRIVIA NIGHT AT THE BAR.

12:07.227 --> 12:08.298
WHAT?

12:08.298 --> 12:10.300
DUDE KNOWS HIS HISTORY.

12:10.300 --> 12:11.201
Leon: THANK YOU.

12:11.201 --> 12:13.233
YOU TOOK HIM OUT
WITH YOU LAST NIGHT?

12:13.233 --> 12:13.904
ARE YOU INSANE?

12:13.904 --> 12:15.836
LISTEN, YOU CAN'T JUST
KEEP HIM COOPED UP

12:15.836 --> 12:18.138
IN YOUR LOCKER ALL DAY
AND NIGHT, IT'S CRUEL.

12:18.138 --> 12:19.339
CRUEL?
SOCK, HE'S A MURDERER.

12:19.339 --> 12:21.812
Leon: IT WAS A MISTAKE.
I REALIZE THAT NOW.

12:21.812 --> 12:24.074
IT WAS ALL MISDIRECTED ANGER.

12:24.074 --> 12:26.246
I WASN'T MAD
AT PRESIDENT MCKINLEY,

12:26.246 --> 12:27.277
I WAS MAD AT MY FATHER.

12:27.277 --> 12:29.079
SEE? THERAPY'S
WORKING WONDERS.

12:29.079 --> 12:29.980
LAST NIGHT AT THE BAR,

12:29.980 --> 12:33.323
HE WAS TOTALLY HELPING
ME THROUGH ALL MY MOTHER
ISSUES LAST NIGHT.

12:33.323 --> 12:34.825
WHAT MOTHER ISSUES?

12:34.825 --> 12:37.157
WELL...

12:40.130 --> 12:42.762
THE BREAST FEEDING.

12:42.993 --> 12:44.334
AND HOW I NEVER WANTED
TO STOP.

12:44.334 --> 12:48.168
AND LEON EXPLAINED TO ME
THAT THAT IS OK. I'M OK.

12:48.168 --> 12:49.769
Leon: AND I CAN
HELP YOU TOO, SAM.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.201
TELL ME
ABOUT YOUR CHILDHOOD.

12:51.201 --> 12:53.473
MY PARENTS SOLD MY SOUL
TO THE DEVIL.

12:53.473 --> 12:55.045
Leon: SO. OHH. UH, WELL,

12:55.045 --> 12:58.778
THAT'S SOME ABANDONMENT
AND BETRAYAL...

12:58.778 --> 13:02.182
AND I'M GONNA GUESS THERE
WAS A LOT OF BED-WETTING.

13:02.182 --> 13:03.183
OK.
LISTEN, LISTEN.

13:03.183 --> 13:08.088
THE POINT IS,
LEON IS TRYING TO MAKE
HIMSELF A BETTER PERSON.

13:08.088 --> 13:12.162
OK? HE MADE MISTAKES. JUST
LIKE YOU MADE A MISTAKE.

13:12.162 --> 13:15.265
DOESN'T EVERYBODY DESERVE
FORGIVENESS, HMM?

13:15.265 --> 13:17.397
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

13:19.569 --> 13:20.931
HEY, TED.

13:20.931 --> 13:22.973
HOW COME YOU DIDN'T
DRESS UP FOR HALLOWEEN?

13:22.973 --> 13:24.504
HA HA HA HA.

13:24.504 --> 13:26.276
PUMPKIN COSTUME
IS IN MY OFFICE, SAM.

13:26.276 --> 13:28.208
THANK ME LATER FOR
HAVING IT DRY CLEANED.

13:28.208 --> 13:32.582
THE LAST PUMPKIN WAS
QUITE THE SWEATY BETTY.

13:37.287 --> 13:40.350
SCARE UP SOME SAVINGS
AT THE BENCH.

13:41.221 --> 13:44.855
SCARE UP SOME SAVINGS
AT THE BENCH. 30%...

13:44.855 --> 13:47.297
I HATE THIS COSTUME.
IT'S SO HUMILIATING.

13:47.297 --> 13:50.830
WELL, I THINK YOU LOOK LIKE
A VERY PRETTY PUMPKIN.

13:50.830 --> 13:52.402
I LOOK LIKE AN IDIOT.

13:52.402 --> 13:53.003
NO, YOU DON'T.

13:53.003 --> 13:57.337
YOU KNOW, LEON SAID
THAT YOU MIGHT HAVE SOME
SELF-ESTEEM ISSUES,

13:57.337 --> 13:59.839
AND I CAN
CLEARLY SEE THAT NOW.

13:59.839 --> 14:01.311
ENOUGH WITH LEON ALREADY.

14:01.311 --> 14:02.312
SCARE UP
SOME SAVINGS AT THE--

14:02.312 --> 14:03.874
HE'S RIGHT THOUGH.
LOOK AT YOU.

14:03.874 --> 14:05.345
YOU'RE EMBARRASSED,
YOU'RE ALL AFRAID

14:05.345 --> 14:06.376
THAT PEOPLE WILL
LOOK YOU IN THE EYE.

14:06.376 --> 14:09.849
THIS IS NOT THE SAM I KNOW.
THANK YOU. YOU'RE NOT HELPING!

14:09.849 --> 14:13.353
YOU KNOW, YOU ARE LETTING
THE PUMPKIN OWN YOU.

14:13.353 --> 14:16.226
YOU NEED TO OWN THE PUMPKIN.

14:16.226 --> 14:17.357
YOU OWN THE PUMPKIN.

14:17.357 --> 14:19.029
EXCUSE ME?
YOU OWN THE PUMPKIN.

14:19.029 --> 14:20.260
I WOULD KILL TO OWN
THE PUMPKIN, OK?

14:20.260 --> 14:22.392
I WOULD KILL SOMEBODY TO BE
IN YOUR PLACE RIGHT NOW.

14:22.392 --> 14:25.365
EMBARRASSMENT DOES
NOT COMPUTE UP HERE, SAM.

14:25.365 --> 14:27.037
MATTER OF FACT--AHEM...

14:27.037 --> 14:31.041
I THINK I MIGHT GET INTO
MY HALLOWEEN COSTUME RIGHT NOW.

14:31.041 --> 14:33.273
WHAT'S THAT?
WHAT ARE YOU--

14:33.273 --> 14:34.144
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

14:34.144 --> 14:36.306
GETTING INTO MY COSTUME.
I JUST TOLD YOU.

14:36.306 --> 14:39.449
AH! I AM UNDERWEAR MAN.

14:39.950 --> 14:41.311
I'M UNDERWEAR MAN.

14:41.311 --> 14:43.583
GIVE ME THE FLYERS,
GIVE THEM, GIVE THEM.

14:43.583 --> 14:45.515
LISTEN TO ME, SAM.
LISTEN TO ME.

14:45.515 --> 14:47.257
IF SOMEONE TRIES
TO HUMILIATE YOU,

14:47.257 --> 14:50.190
ALL YOU NEED TO DO IS JUST
LOOK THAT PERSON IN THE EYE

14:50.190 --> 14:50.991
AND HUMILIATE THEM RIGHT BACK.

14:50.991 --> 14:54.664
SHOW THEM YOU'RE THE CAT'S NUTS.
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

14:54.664 --> 14:57.397
WATCH THIS. HI, THERE.

14:57.397 --> 15:00.530
WELCOME TO THE WORK BENCH.
HAPPY HALLOWEEN.

15:03.273 --> 15:06.276
TOTALLY DOMINATED THAT GUY.
SEE? IT'S THAT EASY.

15:06.276 --> 15:08.138
YOU FEEL BETTER
ABOUT BEING THE PUMPKIN?

15:08.138 --> 15:09.339
YEAH, YEAH. I KINDA DO.

15:09.339 --> 15:11.281
IT'S ACTUALLY
KINDA LIBERATING.

15:11.281 --> 15:14.444
I CAN FEEL
EVERY LITTLE BREEZE.

15:16.486 --> 15:18.188
LET'S CHECK IT OUT.

15:18.188 --> 15:19.349
COME ON, COME ON.

15:19.349 --> 15:22.092
ALL RIGHT. OPEN IT UP.

15:27.127 --> 15:29.159
WHAT IS IT?

15:29.960 --> 15:31.701
[DOG GROWLING]

15:34.204 --> 15:35.935
SOME KIND
OF THERMOMETER.

15:35.935 --> 15:37.137
IT'S A MEAT THERMOMETER.

15:37.137 --> 15:39.970
YOU STAB IT INTO A POT ROAST,
TURKEY OR SOMETHING.

15:39.970 --> 15:41.541
RIGHT, RIGHT.
THE BUTCHER.

15:41.541 --> 15:42.312
MEAT. MAKES SENSE.

15:42.312 --> 15:44.374
THE BUTCHER? THAT'S
A PRETTY GOOD NAME.

15:44.374 --> 15:46.276
YEAH. IF I WAS
A SERIAL KILLER,

15:46.276 --> 15:47.717
I'D WANT MY NAME TO BE
SOMETHING MORE EFFECTIVE

15:47.717 --> 15:49.149
LIKE MURDER MAN AND KILLBOT.

15:49.149 --> 15:50.720
WELL, IT SEEMS
USER-FRIENDLY.

15:50.720 --> 15:55.255
STAB IT INTO THE SOUL'S
TRACHEA, NO PROBLEM.

15:55.255 --> 15:56.386
[GROWLING]

15:56.386 --> 15:57.187
WHAT'S WITH THE HELL HOUND?

15:57.187 --> 15:59.529
I THINK HE'S SUPPOSED TO
HELP US FIND THE SOUL.

15:59.529 --> 16:03.193
SO HOW DO
WE NAB THE BUTCHER?

16:03.193 --> 16:03.593
FIND HIS HIDE-OUT.

16:03.593 --> 16:05.095
I DON'T KNOW WHERE THE DEVIL
TOOK ME LAST NIGHT,

16:05.095 --> 16:07.237
BUT FOR A CHANGE,
HE GAVE ME A LOT OF
BACKGROUND ON THE GUY.

16:07.237 --> 16:09.669
GOOD. LET'S LOOK HIM UP.

16:15.345 --> 16:17.447
WE NEED THE COMPUTER.

16:17.447 --> 16:18.078
NO.

16:18.078 --> 16:20.210
HEY, THEY GOT
SOME CANDY UP FRONT.

16:20.210 --> 16:21.311
YOU WANT SOME CANDY?

16:21.311 --> 16:22.352
DON'T CARE.

16:22.352 --> 16:23.413
ALL RIGHT. I TRIED.

16:23.413 --> 16:25.685
COME ON.
YOU'RE OUT OF HERE.

16:25.685 --> 16:27.417
TYPE, BEN,

16:33.063 --> 16:34.364
FOUND THIS ON A SERIAL
KILLER WEBSITE.

16:34.364 --> 16:38.128
"BARNEY KIRKWOOD, A-K-A
THE BUTCHER OF BALLARD,

16:38.128 --> 16:41.071
"A PARTICULARLY BRUTAL KILLER,
ACTIVE IN THE FORTIES.

16:41.071 --> 16:45.235
NEARLY ESCAPED PROSECUTION
BECAUSE THE BODIES
WERE NEVER FOUND."

16:45.235 --> 16:46.776
THAT'S HIM, THAT'S WHO
THE DEVIL WAS TALKING ABOUT.

16:46.776 --> 16:50.580
NOW THEY THINK
HE CHOPPED UP HIS VICTIMS
AND FED THEM TO HIS DOGS.

16:50.580 --> 16:51.341
NOW THAT'S GROSS.

16:51.341 --> 16:53.443
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO
BE THE HELPER, HUH?
WHERE IS HE?

16:53.443 --> 16:55.115
HE IS CALLED
THE BUTCHER OF BALLARD.

16:55.115 --> 16:56.646
AND BALLARD IS ONLY
A FEW MILES AWAY.

16:56.646 --> 17:00.019
LET'S GO.
YEAH. LET'S DO IT.

17:00.390 --> 17:01.421
NO, I THINK WE'RE WRONG.

17:01.421 --> 17:03.523
THIS ISN'T WHERE
THE DEVIL TOOK ME.

17:03.523 --> 17:04.724
LOOKS COMPLETELY DIFFERENT.

17:04.724 --> 17:06.356
I DON'T KNOW,
THEN IF...

17:06.356 --> 17:09.729
HE'S IN ANOTHER
NEIGHBORHOOD,
WE'RE SCREWED.

17:09.729 --> 17:12.532
LOOK AT THAT.

17:16.436 --> 17:17.407
"REBECCA CASHMAN."

17:17.407 --> 17:21.641
"LAST SEEN LEAVING
WORK AT THE FLOWER MARKET
TWO NIGHTS AGO."

17:21.641 --> 17:23.273
HMM.

17:25.445 --> 17:27.377
WAIT A SECOND. THIS IS IT.

17:27.377 --> 17:29.419
THIS IS WHERE HE TOOK ME.

17:29.419 --> 17:33.423
YOU THINK HE'S STILL
GOT THE MISSING GIRL?

17:33.423 --> 17:34.284
I DOUBT IT.

17:34.284 --> 17:36.086
SAID HE'D ALREADY
KILLED ONCE.

17:36.086 --> 17:38.388
BUT HE'S COMING
BACK TONIGHT.

17:38.388 --> 17:40.390
[WOLF HOWLING]

17:42.292 --> 17:44.634
THANK GOD IT'S NOT
A FULL MOON TONIGHT.

17:44.634 --> 17:46.496
YEAH, I WOULD HATE
TO HAVE TO CATCH

17:46.496 --> 17:48.738
THE BUTCHER
UNDER A FULL MOON.

17:48.738 --> 17:49.639
MM-HMM.

17:49.639 --> 17:51.801
IT'S GETTING LATE,
WE SHOULD HEAD--

17:51.801 --> 17:53.143
HAVE YOU SEEN SOCK?

17:53.143 --> 17:56.446
NO, HE DISAPPEARED
AS SOON AS WE GOT BACK.

17:58.278 --> 17:59.809
[LAUGHTER]

18:03.353 --> 18:04.354
HEY.

18:04.354 --> 18:05.285
HEY.

18:05.285 --> 18:06.085
WHAT'S UP?

18:06.085 --> 18:11.090
WHAT? NOTHING. I WAS JUST
REMEMBERING A REALLY FUNNY
THING THAT HAPPENED.

18:11.090 --> 18:12.292
OH, YEAH? WHAT?

18:12.292 --> 18:13.623
UH...I WAS JUST...

18:13.623 --> 18:17.767
HAVING A PRIVATE MOMENT--
LITTLE JOKE FOR MYSELF.

18:17.767 --> 18:19.369
YOU HAVE BRAIN DAMAGE.

18:19.369 --> 18:23.273
MAYBE...PROBABLY.

18:26.836 --> 18:27.737
ALL RIGHT. SO, GO ON.

18:27.737 --> 18:30.580
Leon: SO, TED HEARS MY VOICE
COMING OUT OF HIS TOILET.

18:30.580 --> 18:32.612
AND HE SAYS,
GOD, IS THAT YOU?

18:32.612 --> 18:35.385
AND I SAID, YES, TED.
THIS IS GOD.

18:35.385 --> 18:37.317
AND I'VE GOT
ABE LINCOLN WITH ME

18:37.317 --> 18:40.620
AND WE BOTH THINK YOU'RE
A HUGE DOUCHE BAG.

18:40.620 --> 18:42.652
AND THEN HE STARTED
CRYING, GOING,

18:42.652 --> 18:46.826
OOH, OOH, HONEST ABE,
PLEASE FORGIVE ME.

18:48.398 --> 18:52.402
SO, UH, SO, WHAT DOES
THE BUTCHER LOOK LIKE NOW?

18:52.402 --> 18:54.464
I DON'T KNOW...

18:55.505 --> 18:56.766
[DOG BARKING]

18:56.766 --> 18:57.767
WHAT IS IT?
WHAT IS IT?

18:57.767 --> 18:59.809
WHOA.
LASSIE'S GOING NUTS.

18:59.809 --> 19:01.911
[DOG GROWLING]

19:02.312 --> 19:03.813
OH, SAM,
IS THAT YOU?

19:03.813 --> 19:05.175
ARE YOU PLAYING A JOKE?

19:05.175 --> 19:06.916
IT'S NOT FUNNY.

19:07.547 --> 19:09.919
[ROARING]
LOOK!

19:12.182 --> 19:13.453
[LOUD ROARING]

19:13.453 --> 19:14.854
I GOT TO STAB IT!

19:14.854 --> 19:16.426
GO, GO, GO!

19:21.331 --> 19:22.562
SAM. LISTEN,
SAM, WHAT DO WE DO?

19:22.562 --> 19:25.335
I HAVE TO GET CLOSE ENOUGH,
BUT THAT'S INSANE, SAM!

19:25.335 --> 19:26.366
JUST WAIT.
MAYBE IT WENT AWAY.

19:26.366 --> 19:29.769
MAYBE IT THINKS WE LEFT.
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

19:35.245 --> 19:36.406
OH!

19:36.406 --> 19:39.449
[ROARING]

19:41.851 --> 19:43.213
IT'S COMING!

19:43.213 --> 19:44.214
GRAB IT NOW.

19:44.214 --> 19:45.315
I GOT TO DO SOMETHING.

19:45.315 --> 19:46.786
DO IT NOW, SAM.
DO IT NOW.

19:46.786 --> 19:50.920
[ROARING]

19:54.494 --> 19:55.325
LOOK OUT!

19:55.325 --> 19:57.297
AAH! I DROPPED IT, I THINK.

19:57.297 --> 20:00.770
I LOST THE VESSEL!
I LOST THE VESSEL!

20:01.431 --> 20:02.432
[ROARING]

20:02.432 --> 20:04.574
I'LL SEE YOU IN HELL, BUDDY.

20:06.936 --> 20:07.877
SHH, SHH.

20:07.877 --> 20:10.310
[DOG BARKING]

20:18.217 --> 20:20.620
SPIKE. HA HA HA HA!

20:20.620 --> 20:22.752
OHH, OHH.

20:22.752 --> 20:24.424
[LAUGHTER]

20:24.424 --> 20:26.426
OHH. OHH.

20:26.426 --> 20:28.358
GOOD DOG.

20:34.434 --> 20:36.736
YOU ARE NUMBER ONE!
YOU ARE THE CHAMPION! AHH!

20:36.736 --> 20:40.270
I'VE NEVER BEEN SO AFRAID
IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

20:40.270 --> 20:41.341
WHAT WAS IT?

20:41.341 --> 20:42.472
THE BUTCHER. HELL
MUST'VE TURNED HIM

20:42.472 --> 20:44.344
INTO SOME KIND OF DOG
MONSTER OR SOMETHING.

20:44.344 --> 20:45.375
PRETZELS FOR THE HERO, HUH?

20:45.375 --> 20:47.347
YOU SAVED OUR ASSES!
TAKE THAT, TAKE THAT.

20:47.347 --> 20:49.379
YOU KNOW, I'M GONNA
HAVE TO GET UP
CLOSE AND PERSONAL

20:49.379 --> 20:50.950
WITH THAT THING IF I'M
EVER GONNA CAPTURE IT.

20:50.950 --> 20:53.423
THAT'S SUICIDE.
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

20:53.423 --> 20:54.253
I HAVE AN IDEA.

20:54.253 --> 20:55.825
YOU'RE GONNA HATE
THIS IDEA BUT...

20:55.825 --> 20:57.327
TELL ME. ANYTHING.
RIGHT NOW.

20:57.327 --> 20:59.889
ALL RIGHT. I SAY WE ASK
LEON FOR HELP.

21:00.690 --> 21:01.861
NO, NO!

21:01.861 --> 21:02.392
WHY? SAM!

21:02.392 --> 21:03.993
WE WANTS TO HELP US.
HE KNOWS THINGS.

21:03.993 --> 21:06.466
HE'S AN ESCAPED SOUL, TOO.

21:06.466 --> 21:06.966
YOU BROUGHT HIM?!

21:06.966 --> 21:09.469
WHAT? HE WAITED IN THE CAR,
HE'S FINE.

21:09.469 --> 21:10.340
LISTEN, LISTEN, LEON.

21:10.340 --> 21:11.801
LEON, JUST TELL HIM
WHAT YOU TOLD ME. GO.

21:11.801 --> 21:15.545
Leon: I WAS JUST
SAYING, I THINK I KNOW
THIS "BUTCHER" GUY.

21:15.545 --> 21:17.947
HE USED TO HANG
WITH SOME FRIENDS OF MINE.

21:17.947 --> 21:18.508
RIGHT, RIGHT.

21:18.508 --> 21:19.479
ALL THE BAZILLIONS
OF PEOPLE IN HELL,

21:19.479 --> 21:21.311
AND YOU KNEW
THIS GUY. THE ONE GUY
WE'RE LOOKING FOR.

21:21.311 --> 21:24.414
SAM, I CAN TELL YOU'RE
UNDER A LOT OF STRESS,

21:24.414 --> 21:25.385
AND THAT MUST BE
DIFFICULT FOR YOU--

21:25.385 --> 21:28.057
STOP TALKING! WHY DO YOU
LISTEN TO THIS GUY, HUH?

21:28.057 --> 21:29.359
WHY? DO YOU HAVE
A BETTER PLAN, SAM?

21:29.359 --> 21:32.592
SAM, MAYBE WE SHOULD
REALLY CONSIDER
LETTING HIM HELP US.

21:32.592 --> 21:35.865
I MEAN, MAYBE HE REALLY
IS REHABILITATED.

21:35.865 --> 21:38.328
MAN, COME ON.

21:38.328 --> 21:39.298
EVEN GOD FORGIVES SINS.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.331
I MEAN, AND IF YOU'RE
TRULY REPENTANT.

21:41.331 --> 21:42.402
IF YOU'RE TRULY CHANGED,

21:42.402 --> 21:44.974
I MEAN, IS IT FAIR THAT YOU
SPEND AN ETERNITY IN HELL?

21:44.974 --> 21:48.608
I CAN'T BELIEVE--
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

21:53.312 --> 21:54.584
EXCUSE ME! HI!

21:54.584 --> 21:56.816
I NEED SOMEBODY TO TAKE
THIS SOUL! CAN YOU, UH--

21:56.816 --> 21:58.488
CAN YOU SEND
SOMEONE UP PLEASE?

21:58.488 --> 22:00.420
NO? NO, HEY, LISTEN.

22:00.420 --> 22:01.351
I NEED--I NEED SOMEBODY
TO TAKE THIS SOUL.

22:01.351 --> 22:05.024
I'M GONNA KILL HIM! CAN YOU
GET THE DEVIL FOR ME PLEASE?

22:05.024 --> 22:06.856
I JUST NEED TO TALK
TO THE DEVIL.

22:06.856 --> 22:08.528
WHAT ARE YOU DOING? NO.

22:08.528 --> 22:09.399
AHH.

22:09.399 --> 22:11.501
Leon: HAVE EVER YOU
THOUGHT ABOUT SOME

22:11.501 --> 22:13.833
ANTI-ANXIET MEDICATIONS,
SAM, OR YOGA,

22:13.833 --> 22:16.466
OR MAYBE JOURNALING?
I MEAN, THAT'S--

22:16.466 --> 22:17.336
SHUT UP.

22:17.336 --> 22:18.968
[DOG BARKING IN BACKGROUND]

22:33.523 --> 22:34.384
WHAT THE...

22:34.384 --> 22:36.085
WELL, DON'T LOOK SO SURPRISED.

22:36.085 --> 22:38.458
YOU'RE THE ONE THAT
WANTED TO TALK TO ME.

22:38.458 --> 22:39.989
CAN YOU--
CAN YOU GO?

22:39.989 --> 22:42.532
OH, PLEASE WITH THE MODESTY.

22:42.532 --> 22:47.637
I'M LIKE A DOCTOR, SAM, IT ALL
LOOKS LIKE RAW MEAT TO ME.

22:52.972 --> 22:54.974
OHH.

22:55.605 --> 22:57.477
HEY, LISTEN, AS A FRIEND,

22:57.477 --> 23:00.780
I GOT TO TELL YOU,
YOU'RE LOSING IT, MAN.

23:00.780 --> 23:01.911
TAKE HIM TO HELL.

23:01.911 --> 23:03.913
PLEASE.
TAKE HIM AWAY.

23:03.913 --> 23:05.154
THERE'S NOBODY DOWN
THERE TO GIVE HIM TO.

23:05.154 --> 23:08.788
YOU JUST HAVE TO WAIT
UNTIL HALLOWEEN'S OVER
LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE.

23:08.788 --> 23:09.158
JUST ONE MORE DAY.

23:09.158 --> 23:12.792
WELL, CAN'T YOU JUST HOLD ON
TO HIM THEN TILL THEN ?

23:12.792 --> 23:13.963
WHAT'S THE BIG RUSH?

23:13.963 --> 23:15.024
HE WON'T STOP TALKING.

23:15.024 --> 23:16.395
HE'S MAKING ME FIGHT
WITH MY FRIENDS.

23:16.395 --> 23:18.397
I JUST--I REALLY
NEED HIM TO GO AWAY.

23:18.397 --> 23:20.830
HOW'S THE GIRL?

23:21.130 --> 23:22.432
SHE'S NOT TALKING TO ME.

23:22.432 --> 23:24.003
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

23:24.003 --> 23:25.404
SAM...

23:25.404 --> 23:27.507
IF I CAN IMPART TO YOU
ONE PIECE OF KNOWLEDGE,

23:27.507 --> 23:29.178
JUST ONE KERNEL
OF TRUTH THAT I'VE GLEANED

23:29.178 --> 23:32.982
OVER THE ENTIRETY OF MY
EXISTENCE, IT WOULD BE THIS:

23:32.982 --> 23:37.416
BETRAYAL IS THE DEFINING
TRAIT OF HUMANITY.

23:37.416 --> 23:39.989
YOUR FRIENDS WILL
ALWAYS LET YOU DOWN.

23:39.989 --> 23:41.851
THE GIRL WILL ALWAYS LEAVE.

23:41.851 --> 23:43.893
THAT'S NOT TRUE.
YES, IT IS.

23:43.893 --> 23:47.096
AND YOUR SO-CALLED FRIENDS
ARE PROVING MY POINT.

23:47.096 --> 23:49.198
YOU'RE NOT ANGRY AT LEON.

23:49.198 --> 23:52.462
YOU'RE JUST UPSET
BECAUSE YOU'RE REALIZING

23:52.462 --> 23:53.463
THE WEAKNESS OF YOUR SPECIES.

23:53.463 --> 23:59.869
THE MOST UNTRUSTWORTHY,
UNRELIABLE CREATURES
ON THIS EARTH...

23:59.869 --> 24:02.672
EXCEPT FOR BEARS.

24:03.543 --> 24:05.044
I KNOW THIS IS A HARD
LESSON FOR YOU TO TAKE,

24:05.044 --> 24:06.976
AND I'M SORRY I HAVE
TO BE THE ONE TO TEACH YOU.

24:06.976 --> 24:11.150
BUT IT'S BEST
YOU UNDERSTAND NOW.

24:11.781 --> 24:14.153
YOU KNOW, IN A WAY,

24:14.153 --> 24:17.557
I'M THE MOST
TRUSTWORTHY PERSON YOU KNOW.

24:17.557 --> 24:18.958
AND THAT'S JUST SAD.

24:18.958 --> 24:21.230
[CLOCK CHIMES]

24:21.230 --> 24:22.131
NO.

24:22.131 --> 24:24.664
GOODY. MIDNIGHT

24:24.664 --> 24:27.867
HAPPY HALLOWEEN.

24:27.867 --> 24:29.468
MMM.

24:29.468 --> 24:30.940
HAPPY HALLOWEEN!

24:30.940 --> 24:32.602
SCARE UP SOME
SAVINGS AT THE BENCH.

24:32.602 --> 24:36.475
YOU WANT A SCARE--NO, YOU
DON'T WANT TO SCARE UP...

24:36.475 --> 24:37.176
HEY, ANDI.

24:37.176 --> 24:38.477
HEY.

24:38.477 --> 24:39.649
YOU ON BREAK?

24:39.649 --> 24:40.209
UH, NO.

24:40.209 --> 24:41.150
TED WANTS YOU TO GO
TO THE LOADING DOCK

24:41.150 --> 24:43.853
WHEN YOU'RE DONE HERE TO
HELP WITH A SHIPMENT.

24:43.853 --> 24:45.084
OK. GREAT.
OK.

24:45.084 --> 24:45.615
WAIT! UH...

24:45.615 --> 24:47.186
ARE YOU GOING TO ANY
HALLOWEEN PARTIES TONIGHT?

24:47.186 --> 24:48.157
'CAUSE I WAS THINKING...

24:48.157 --> 24:53.222
YOU KNOW, I THINK
WE SHOULD JUST TALK
ABOUT WORK STUFF. ONLY.

24:53.222 --> 24:54.524
FROM NOW ON.

24:54.524 --> 24:55.595
UH, YEAH. YEAH, GREAT.

24:55.595 --> 24:57.997
YES. LET'S TALK ABOUT WORK.

24:57.997 --> 24:59.098
TONIGHT, HAVE A COUPLE BEERS.

24:59.098 --> 25:01.200
I CAN PRACTICE MY SALES PITCH
ON AIR CONDITIONER FILTERS.

25:01.200 --> 25:03.833
I THINK IT MIGHT CHANGE THE WAY
YOU LOOK AT THE WORLD.

25:03.833 --> 25:04.734
NO, SAM.

25:04.734 --> 25:07.006
WORK TALK SHOULD
STAY AT WORK.

25:07.006 --> 25:09.579
BECAUSE THOSE ARE
THE NEW RULES.

25:09.579 --> 25:13.042
I...I THINK THOSE
RULES ARE STUPID.

25:13.042 --> 25:14.544
OK. WELL...

25:14.544 --> 25:18.818
IT'S NOT ABOUT
WHAT YOU THINK, SAM.

25:20.149 --> 25:21.851
WHY NOT?

25:21.851 --> 25:24.824
ANDI! WHY NOT?!

25:39.008 --> 25:40.309
SON OF A BITCH.

25:40.309 --> 25:43.813
SOCK! LEON'S GONE!
HE GOT OUT!

25:43.813 --> 25:47.817
OK, OK. DON'T BE MAD.
ALL RIGHT?

25:47.817 --> 25:50.319
HANDS UP.

25:53.252 --> 25:56.786
[HIGH VOICE]
HI, SAM. DID I SCARE YOU?

25:56.786 --> 25:58.788
[REGULAR VOICE]
SAY HIM YOU'RE SORRY.

25:58.788 --> 26:01.661
[HIGH VOICE]
I'M SORRY.

26:01.661 --> 26:04.664
I'M HERE TO HELP.

26:11.941 --> 26:12.902
TAKE IT EASY!
HEY! GUYS, GUYS!

26:12.902 --> 26:14.273
EVERYTHING'S COOL HERE.
EVERYTHING'S COOL.

26:14.273 --> 26:16.105
NO, NO EVERYTHING IS COOL!
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

26:16.105 --> 26:17.847
SAM, I SAID
DON'T BE MAD.

26:17.847 --> 26:19.178
AND I SAID,
DO NOT TO TOUCH HIM!

26:19.178 --> 26:21.681
SEE, GUYS, WHEN YOU PLAY
THE BLAME GAME, NOBODY WINS.

26:21.681 --> 26:24.313
STOP, STOP, STOP WITH THE
STUPID THERAPY CRAP, OK?!

26:24.313 --> 26:26.616
SAM, HE IS TRYING
TO HELP US.

26:26.616 --> 26:27.957
OK, SOCK, SOCK, MY MAN.

26:27.957 --> 26:31.220
LISTEN, I AM SAM'S
RESPONSIBILITY.

26:31.220 --> 26:32.762
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?
HOW ABOUT--

26:32.762 --> 26:34.924
HOW ABOUT
I PROVE MYSELF TO YOU?

26:34.924 --> 26:35.995
HOW ARE YOU GOING
TO DO THAT?

26:35.995 --> 26:38.628
WELL, YOU KNOW, THIS
GUY THAT YOU'RE AFTER,

26:38.628 --> 26:41.170
MAINLY ATTACKS AT NIGHT.
MY THEORY IS,

26:41.170 --> 26:43.072
HE'S A DAY SLEEPER.

26:43.072 --> 26:44.033
SO?

26:44.033 --> 26:46.976
SO, YOU FIND HIM DURING
THE DAY WHEN HE'S SLEEPING,

26:46.976 --> 26:49.308
THE ELEMENT OF SURPRISE.
BOOM, YOU'VE GOT HIM.

26:49.308 --> 26:51.981
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
IF I'M WRONG, IF I'M WRONG,

26:51.981 --> 26:54.613
I'LL GO GET BACK
IN THAT VESSEL MYSELF. OK?

26:54.613 --> 26:56.615
NO COMPLAINTS,
AND IF I'M RIGHT...

26:56.615 --> 27:01.921
WELL, WE'RE WORK OUT, YOU
KNOW, WHAT MY REWARD IS.

27:04.794 --> 27:05.895
UH...

27:05.895 --> 27:06.625
I'M BRINGING THE VESSEL.

27:06.625 --> 27:10.299
ONE STUPID MOVE AND YOU'RE
GOING BACK INSIDE. I'M...

27:11.030 --> 27:13.102
LET'S GO FOR A RIDE.

27:14.934 --> 27:19.208
SO...YOU GUYS BEEN
FRIENDS A LONG TIME?

27:22.041 --> 27:23.642
GUYS, THIS
MAKES ME SAD.

27:23.642 --> 27:26.415
I FEEL LIKE I'M THE SOURCE
OF ALL THIS CONFLICT.

27:26.415 --> 27:28.778
CAN YOU PLEASE
JUST STOP TALKING?

27:28.778 --> 27:32.081
YOU KNOW, I JUST--I JUST
FEEL LIKE--OH, HERE IT IS.

27:32.081 --> 27:34.083
IT'S COMING UP
RIGHT UP HERE.

27:34.083 --> 27:35.184
A CHINESE RESTAURANT?

27:35.184 --> 27:37.326
THE SOUL IS AT
A CHINESE RESTAURANT?

27:37.326 --> 27:38.928
IT'S NOT THAT EASY.

27:38.928 --> 27:39.989
I MEAN,
I GOT TO, YOU KNOW,

27:39.989 --> 27:41.260
TALK TO MY PEOPLE,
FIND OUT WHERE HE IS.

27:41.260 --> 27:44.293
AND--AND, UM...I SHOULD
PROBABLY GO IN ALONE,

27:44.293 --> 27:46.365
YOU KNOW, BEING SEEN
WITH HELL'S BOUNTY HUNTER

27:46.365 --> 27:50.069
MIGHT BE A LITTLE BAD ON MY
STREET CRED. YOU UNDERSTAND?

27:50.069 --> 27:51.941
RIGHT? ALL RIGHT.

27:53.172 --> 27:58.047
HEY, LEON, GRAB ME
SOME MU SHU, WILL YA? LEON!

27:59.678 --> 28:01.310
NEVER MIND!

28:01.310 --> 28:03.913
I'LL JUST STARVE.

28:12.992 --> 28:15.124
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.
I'M GOING IN.

28:15.124 --> 28:16.966
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, HEY!

28:16.966 --> 28:17.897
LISTEN, IF
HE WANTED TO ESCAPE,

28:17.897 --> 28:19.899
HE WOULD'VE AS SOON
AS I LET HIM OUT OF THE VESSEL.

28:19.899 --> 28:22.231
JUST SIT TIGHT. HE'S TRYING
TO HELP US. TRUST ME.

28:22.231 --> 28:24.473
NO, SOCK. CLEARLY,
I CAN'T TRUST YOU.

28:24.473 --> 28:26.936
WHY--WHY WILL YOU NOT
JUST GIVE HIM A CHANCE?

28:26.936 --> 28:28.477
YOU DIDN'T LET HIM OUT
TO GIVE HIM A CHANCE.

28:28.477 --> 28:30.009
YOU LET HIM OUT BECAUSE
YOU THOUGHT HE WAS FUNNY.

28:30.009 --> 28:33.282
ALL RIGHT, OK,
MAYBE THAT DID PLAY
INTO MY DECISION

28:33.282 --> 28:35.044
ON THAT, ALL RIGHT?
BUT I JUST THINK--

28:35.044 --> 28:37.887
NO, SOCK, DON'T THINK!
OK? YOU NEVER THINK!

28:37.887 --> 28:40.489
YOU PLAY WITH A HULA DOLL
AND ALMOST GET US KILLED!

28:40.489 --> 28:43.052
YOU SPEND MORE ENERGY
TRYING TO FIT 75 GUMBALLS

28:43.052 --> 28:44.794
INTO YOUR MOUTH
THAN HELP ME!

28:44.794 --> 28:47.226
IT'S NOT CUTE
ANYMORE, OK?

28:49.959 --> 28:53.032
IT WAS A HUNDRED GUMBALLS.

28:54.503 --> 28:55.765
100.

28:55.765 --> 28:57.967
WHOA. HA HA HA HA.

28:57.967 --> 29:01.911
OH, GOD. LEON NEEDS A NAP.

29:01.911 --> 29:02.842
OHH.

29:02.842 --> 29:03.442
WHERE'S THE BUTCHER?

29:03.442 --> 29:07.346
UH, OH. YOU KNOW HOW TO GET
TO THE PLEASURE PIT?

29:07.346 --> 29:08.477
THE STRIP CLUB?

29:08.477 --> 29:10.119
YES, SIR.
I GOT A HOT TIP.

29:10.119 --> 29:13.222
OH, I HATE THE WAY
YOU SQUEAK THROUGH YOUR
NOSE WHEN YOU BREATHE.

29:13.222 --> 29:16.125
THE STUFF YOU PUT
IN YOUR HAIR MAKES YOU
SMELL LIKE A PIXIE'S ASS.

29:16.125 --> 29:18.487
YOUR MUTANT PINKY TOE.
YOUR ONE BUSHY EYEBROW.

29:18.487 --> 29:20.990
I HATE THE WAY YOU PUT KETCHUP
ON MACARONI AND CHEESE

29:20.990 --> 29:22.061
EVERYTIME YOU EAT IT.

29:22.061 --> 29:25.494
OH, AND YOU WEAR MANDLES.

29:25.494 --> 29:29.038
YOU SAID THE MANDLES
WERE OK.

29:29.038 --> 29:31.100
I LIED, SAM.

29:32.041 --> 29:33.202
THERE WE GO.

29:33.202 --> 29:36.946
HEY, GUYS.
HA HA HA HA!

29:36.946 --> 29:38.107
MMM, MMM!

29:38.107 --> 29:39.849
GUYS, YOU GOT
ONE MORE STOP.

29:39.849 --> 29:41.881
WE ARE REALLY CLOSE,

29:41.881 --> 29:43.412
AND, OH, UM, COULD
WE DROP OFF CINNAMON?

29:43.412 --> 29:46.155
HER PLACE IS ON THE WAY.

29:46.155 --> 29:47.887
HI, GUYS.

29:53.522 --> 29:56.926
YOU KNOW, I THINK
I'M GONNA CATCH THE NEXT
SOUL ON MY OWN.

29:56.926 --> 29:58.968
I THINK THAT'S
A GREAT IDEA.

29:58.968 --> 30:01.070
GOOD.
GOOD.

30:03.302 --> 30:05.975
OHH. OH, YEAH, HEY.

30:05.975 --> 30:06.836
I GOT A LINE ON HIM.

30:06.836 --> 30:09.238
BRING THE VESSEL.
IT'S GOING DOWN.

30:16.045 --> 30:18.547
WELL, WE'RE HERE.

30:18.547 --> 30:19.188
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

30:19.188 --> 30:22.091
YOU TOOK US ALL OVER TOWN
TO BRING US BACK HERE?!

30:22.091 --> 30:23.322
I TOLD YOU, I HAD
TO TALK TO SOME--

30:23.322 --> 30:27.126
WE'VE ALREADY BEEN HERE, LEON!
WE KNOW THIS PLACE.

30:27.556 --> 30:30.930
I AM SUCH AN IDIOT!

30:30.930 --> 30:33.062
FOLLOW ME.

30:38.507 --> 30:40.369
[GRUNTING]

30:42.071 --> 30:42.611
HA HA! BOOM!

30:42.611 --> 30:45.074
HOW'D YOU KNOW
ABOUT THIS PLACE?

30:45.074 --> 30:48.317
I TOLD YOU.
I KNOW PEOPLE.

30:48.317 --> 30:50.519
OH, MAN. HE'S THERE.

30:50.519 --> 30:52.221
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S DO THIS.

30:52.221 --> 30:54.053
DO YOU HAVE
A FLASHLIGHT?

30:54.053 --> 30:55.024
OF COURSE.

30:55.024 --> 30:57.086
[GUN COCKS]

31:02.261 --> 31:03.432
DUDE, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?

31:03.432 --> 31:05.094
THIS IS NOT ABOUT YOU, SOCK.

31:05.094 --> 31:09.598
SO, I'M STILL GOING TO HELL
AFTER ALL THIS IS OVER?

31:09.598 --> 31:11.040
LEON, PUT
THE GUN DOWN, MAN.

31:11.040 --> 31:13.002
YOU KNOW I HAVE TO SEND
YOU BACK, LEON.

31:13.002 --> 31:14.543
OK. HAND OVER THE VESSEL.

31:14.543 --> 31:15.544
WHAT?

31:15.544 --> 31:18.207
WHOA, WHOA. SLOW DOWN.
THIS IS NUTS. OK?

31:18.207 --> 31:20.179
HAND IT OVER!

31:28.087 --> 31:30.960
NOW GET IN THE HOLE.

31:31.160 --> 31:33.022
THAT THING WILL KILL
US, LEON.

31:33.022 --> 31:35.664
NO, NOT YOU.
JUST THE BOUNTY HUNTER.

31:35.664 --> 31:37.166
LEON, YOU DON'T
WANT TO DO THIS.

31:37.166 --> 31:40.129
I KNOW I DON'T.
THAT'S WHY I'M GOING

31:40.129 --> 31:41.600
TO LET DOG BOY
DO IT FOR ME.

31:41.600 --> 31:44.133
SOCK, COME ON,
STOP MESSING AROUND.

31:44.133 --> 31:46.405
LISTEN, DID YOU REALLY
THINK I WAS GOING TO LET YOU

31:46.405 --> 31:48.107
PUT MY BEST FRIEND DOWN
THAT HOLE BY HIMSELF?

31:48.107 --> 31:49.979
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:49.979 --> 31:52.011
NO, IF SAM GOES IN,
I'M GOING IN.

31:52.011 --> 31:53.012
SOCK, DON'T.

31:53.012 --> 31:54.443
SAM, JUST STOP.

31:55.314 --> 31:59.688
SOCK, THAT IS...

31:59.688 --> 32:01.650
THAT'S A REALLY
BEAUTIFUL GESTURE.

32:01.650 --> 32:05.454
YOU'RE REALLY DECENT, BUT...

32:05.454 --> 32:07.026
REALLY STUPID.

32:07.026 --> 32:08.327
ALL RIGHT, OK.

32:08.327 --> 32:09.158
OK.

32:09.158 --> 32:11.260
TAKE IT EASY.

32:15.104 --> 32:17.506
BOY, MY THERAPIST...

32:17.506 --> 32:21.110
IS GOING TO BE REALLY
DISAPPOINTED IN ME.

32:34.053 --> 32:36.585
[GROWLING]

32:38.087 --> 32:39.688
I'M GONNA--
I'M GONNA HUG YOU, OK?

32:39.688 --> 32:40.589
YEAH, OK.

32:40.589 --> 32:41.960
LIKE A MAN HUG?

32:41.960 --> 32:44.493
YEAH, THAT'D BE NICE.

32:44.493 --> 32:46.665
MMM!

32:46.665 --> 32:47.636
SAM?

32:47.636 --> 32:48.037
YEAH?

32:48.037 --> 32:51.000
WHAT ARE YOU--
ARE YOU FEELING MY ASS?

32:51.000 --> 32:52.071
NO. NO.

32:52.071 --> 32:53.102
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

32:53.102 --> 32:55.604
THERE'S SOMETHING
IN THE BACKPACK.

32:56.575 --> 32:58.477
[GROWLING]

32:59.708 --> 33:01.750
DO YOU THINK IT'LL
WORK ON THAT THING?

33:01.750 --> 33:01.980
[GROWLING]

33:01.980 --> 33:02.411
AHH! I DON'T KNOW!

33:02.411 --> 33:05.084
LET'S CHUCK IT,
CHUCK IT!

33:05.084 --> 33:07.116
[SCREAMING]
THROW IT!

33:13.662 --> 33:14.993
SOCK!

33:14.993 --> 33:18.027
SOCK! ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

33:18.027 --> 33:19.268
SAM!

33:21.470 --> 33:23.001
SAM!

33:23.001 --> 33:23.402
YEAH!

33:23.402 --> 33:26.035
YEAH!
I FOUND THE VESSEL!

33:26.035 --> 33:28.137
OHH!

33:30.239 --> 33:32.111
THROW IT! THROW IT TO ME!

33:34.012 --> 33:36.014
[GROWLING]

33:37.786 --> 33:40.049
AHH! AHH! SAM!

33:40.049 --> 33:42.521
SOCK!

33:42.521 --> 33:44.353
SPIKE! GOOD DOG!

33:44.353 --> 33:46.595
[BARKING]

33:50.559 --> 33:52.631
AH!

34:01.370 --> 34:02.271
OHH.

34:02.271 --> 34:05.074
OHH! OOH!

34:05.774 --> 34:08.077
OH! SAM!

34:08.077 --> 34:09.148
OH!

34:09.148 --> 34:10.549
OH, GOD!

34:10.549 --> 34:13.352
THAT WAS
INCREDIBLE!

34:13.352 --> 34:15.154
HOLY.

34:15.154 --> 34:18.127
THAT WAS TOO CLOSE.

34:18.127 --> 34:19.558
ARE YOU OK?

34:19.558 --> 34:20.529
HUH?

34:20.529 --> 34:23.462
OH, IT'S JUST
A FLESH WOUND.

34:23.462 --> 34:25.134
YOU?

34:25.134 --> 34:27.065
I THINK SO.

34:27.065 --> 34:30.739
I'M REALLY GLAD
YOU DIDN'T GET EATEN
BY THE DOG MONSTER.

34:30.739 --> 34:34.843
YEAH. I'M GLAD YOU
DIDN'T GET EATEN, TOO.

34:36.675 --> 34:37.746
OHH.

34:37.746 --> 34:41.850
ALL RIGHT. LET'S GO.
COME ON.

34:41.850 --> 34:43.212
OHH.

34:43.212 --> 34:44.613
OH!

34:44.613 --> 34:46.315
OOH! OHH.

34:46.315 --> 34:48.257
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
CARRYING ME?

34:48.257 --> 34:50.619
I TELL YOU, AS SOON AS
I GET MY LEG SEWN BACK ON,

34:50.619 --> 34:53.762
I AM TREATING YOU TO A BIG
FROSTY BEER PRODUCT.

34:53.762 --> 34:55.464
WAIT.
WAHT ABOUT LEON?

34:55.464 --> 34:56.465
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT GUY.

34:56.465 --> 34:58.467
I KNOW EXACTLY WHERE
THAT LITTLE TRAITOR IS.

34:58.467 --> 35:00.329
SO MY FATHER SAYS,

35:00.329 --> 35:02.871
"WHY CAN'T YOU ACT BE
MORE LIKE YOUR BROTHER?"

35:02.871 --> 35:06.405
WHICH THAT--OHH. THAT
JUST HURT. YOU KNOW?

35:06.405 --> 35:08.577
THAT HURT BECAUSE...

35:08.577 --> 35:12.110
MY BROTHER ENDS UP
BEING AN OPIUM ADDICT,

35:12.110 --> 35:13.742
SO, YOU KNOW, THAT DIDN'T
WORK OUT VERY WELL FOR HIM.

35:13.742 --> 35:15.844
PLUS, EVERY TIME--

35:15.844 --> 35:19.488
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

35:22.351 --> 35:23.252
HELLO?

35:23.252 --> 35:26.395
OH, NO. OK.

35:26.395 --> 35:28.827
SECURITY SAYS SOMEONE IS
TRYING TO BREAK INTO MY CAR.

35:28.827 --> 35:30.159
LET ME JUST CHECK ON IT.

35:30.159 --> 35:33.532
OH, YEAH. GO AHEAD.
NO RUSH. NO RUSH.

35:38.837 --> 35:41.470
GUYS! GUYS! HEY!

35:41.470 --> 35:42.871
GUYS, GUYS!

35:42.871 --> 35:43.742
HEY! OH, WOW!

35:43.742 --> 35:46.315
OH, YOU'RE ALIVE!
THAT'S GREAT!

35:46.315 --> 35:48.417
HOW'S THERAPY, LEON?

35:48.417 --> 35:49.318
THERAPY? UH...

35:49.318 --> 35:51.180
IT'S A PROCESS.

35:51.180 --> 35:52.421
HUH. PROCESS. YEAH.

35:52.421 --> 35:54.483
YOU GOT A LOT
OF ISSUES, MAN.

35:54.483 --> 35:55.884
I DO, I DO!

35:55.884 --> 35:57.356
YOU KNOW,
AND IT'S WEIRD,

35:57.356 --> 35:57.926
BECAUSE I'M GENUINELY--

35:57.926 --> 36:01.790
I'M GENUINELY HAPPY
THAT ALL OF YOU GUYS
ARE ALIVE.

36:01.790 --> 36:03.732
THEN, YOU KNOW, I'M SAD

36:03.732 --> 36:06.164
BECAUSE I'M GOING
BACK TO HELL.

36:06.164 --> 36:09.798
SO I'M CARRYING AROUND ALL
THESE CONFLICTING EMOTIONS.

36:09.798 --> 36:11.570
I'M CARRYING
AROUND SEVEN STITCHES.

36:11.570 --> 36:12.841
I WONDER WHAT'S WORSE.

36:12.841 --> 36:15.944
OH, YEAH. I GUESS--
OHH!

36:15.944 --> 36:17.806
NOT THIS TIME, BRO.

36:17.806 --> 36:19.177
GOOD ONE.

36:19.177 --> 36:19.748
[CLICK]

36:19.748 --> 36:22.651
OK. HERE'S
HOW IT'S GOING
TO PLAY, ALL RIGHT?

36:22.651 --> 36:26.685
YOU LET ME GO, AND
I DON'T BLOW YOUR
FRIEND'S FACE OFF.

36:26.685 --> 36:29.858
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO DO THAT, LEON.

36:29.858 --> 36:30.919
YOU COULDN'T DO IT BEFORE.

36:30.919 --> 36:33.362
AND YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO DO IT NOW.

36:33.362 --> 36:36.825
YOU'VE BEEN GOING TO THERAPY.
WORKING HARD ON YOURSELF.

36:36.825 --> 36:39.368
YOU REALLY WANT YOUR
THERAPIST TO COME IN HERE

36:39.368 --> 36:42.200
AND FIND TWO DEAD BODIES
ON THE FLOOR?

36:42.200 --> 36:44.273
OH! SAM.

36:44.903 --> 36:47.336
PUT THE GUN DOWN, LEON.

36:47.936 --> 36:50.979
YOU'RE NOT
THAT PERSON ANYMORE.

37:01.890 --> 37:04.453
YEAH, OK.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

37:04.453 --> 37:06.525
YOU GOT ME.

37:12.931 --> 37:13.962
I'M SORRY. I DIDN'T--

37:13.962 --> 37:16.865
I DIDN'T REALLY WANT
TO BLOW YOUR FACE OFF.

37:16.865 --> 37:17.666
NO PROBLEM.

37:17.666 --> 37:19.938
I DID REALLY WANT
TO BREAK YOUR WRIST THOUGH.

37:19.938 --> 37:21.940
STILL MIGHT.

37:21.940 --> 37:23.942
Leon: I'M STARTING TO THINK
I NEED THE STRUCTURE OF HELL

37:23.942 --> 37:24.913
FOR A LITTLE
WHILE LONGER. YOU KNOW?

37:24.913 --> 37:27.276
I'M GONNA WORK ON MYSELF
DOWN THERE FOR REAL.

37:27.276 --> 37:29.978
MAYBE GO FREUDIAN THIS TIME.
FIVE SESSIONS A WEEK.

37:29.978 --> 37:31.880
I'M GONNA MAKE
YOU PROUD, GUYS.

37:31.880 --> 37:33.582
WE'LL MISS YOU, LEON.

37:33.582 --> 37:35.984
SHH. IT'S OUR TURN.

37:36.985 --> 37:40.729
HEY, GLADYS, YOU LOOK...

37:40.729 --> 37:41.660
ROUGH.

37:41.660 --> 37:43.332
GOOD VACATION?

37:43.332 --> 37:44.963
WE PARTY HARD
IN THE UNDERWORLD.

37:44.963 --> 37:48.837
OH, WOMAN, PLEASE. WE NEED
TO PARTY TOGETHER.

37:50.469 --> 37:52.971
PLACE THE VESSEL
ON THE MAT.

37:52.971 --> 37:54.903
YEAH, UM...

37:54.903 --> 37:57.646
CAN YOU TAKE
GOOD CARE OF IT?

37:57.646 --> 37:59.948
OR THAT, EITHER WAY.

37:59.948 --> 38:02.881
Leon: THIS IS FAIRWELL
AND NOT GOOD-BYE!

38:12.691 --> 38:13.322
I MADE A MISTAKE.

38:13.322 --> 38:16.995
I TOTALLY ADMIT THAT, AND
I HAVE APOLOGIZED FOR THAT,

38:16.995 --> 38:18.427
ON NUMEROUS OCCASIONS.

38:18.427 --> 38:20.369
SAM--
I'M NOT FINISHED.

38:20.369 --> 38:21.930
YOU AND I STARTED
OUT AS FRIENDS,

38:21.930 --> 38:26.475
AND EVEN IF YOU DON'T
THINK IT WAS REAL, I DID.

38:26.475 --> 38:27.576
I STILL DO.

38:27.576 --> 38:28.637
SO YOU HAVE TO FORGIVE ME,

38:28.637 --> 38:32.080
BECAUSE ONE MISTAKE
IS NOT ENOUGH TO JUST
THROW EVERYTHING AWAY.

38:32.080 --> 38:32.841
EVERYBODY SCREWS UP.

38:32.841 --> 38:36.545
I WILL, YOU WILL,
AND I'LL PROBABLY,

38:36.545 --> 38:37.045
DEFINITELY DO IT AGAIN.

38:37.045 --> 38:41.990
BUT I MISS WHAT WE HAD AND I'M
NOT GONNA LET IT GO THAT EASILY.

38:41.990 --> 38:45.354
SO...
YOU PRACTICE
THAT SPEECH?

38:45.354 --> 38:47.426
YEAH, I DID.

38:47.426 --> 38:48.927
IN MY CAR.

38:48.927 --> 38:50.058
GOOD ACOUSTICS.

38:50.058 --> 38:52.701
IT WAS GOOD.

38:52.701 --> 38:56.505
YOU USUALLY DON'T TAKE
A STAND LIKE THAT.

38:56.505 --> 39:00.439
YOU'RE RIGHT. YOU'RE
ABSOLUTELY RIGHT.

39:00.439 --> 39:01.940
YOU DESERVE BETTER.

39:05.474 --> 39:06.815
GOOD, GREAT!

39:06.815 --> 39:08.677
I GOT TO BE HONEST
WITH YOU.

39:08.677 --> 39:10.749
I WAS COMPLETELY
MISERABLE.

39:10.749 --> 39:13.982
I JUST CAN'T STAND
BEING IN A FIGHT.

39:13.982 --> 39:16.485
I'M SO BAD AT IT.

39:16.485 --> 39:18.587
I DON'T KNOW,
YOU'RE PRETTY EFFECTIVE

39:18.587 --> 39:20.659
WITH THE WHOLE
SILENT TREATMENT.

39:20.659 --> 39:23.962
YEAH, BUT I HAVE
A STOMACHACHE ALL DAY.

39:25.534 --> 39:27.836
SO...

39:27.836 --> 39:29.137
WHAT SHOULD WE DO?

39:29.137 --> 39:31.139
WE DO WHAT FRIENDS DO.

39:31.139 --> 39:34.443
WE, UM...

39:34.443 --> 39:36.945
GET A BEER
AFTER WORK TONIGHT?

39:36.945 --> 39:38.877
OK.

39:38.877 --> 39:41.810
YEAH, THAT SOUNDS
REALLY GOOD.

39:41.810 --> 39:44.082
ALL RIGHT.

39:44.082 --> 39:46.915
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

39:53.061 --> 39:55.393
HEY!
YOU LOOK HAPPY.

39:55.393 --> 39:56.665
